-ver="1" data-id="1673241107331" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Assess the shoes' intended use. Running shoes should have more cushioning, arch and ankle support, and high traction, whereas lifting shoes should have a lifted heel and a flat sole to give stability and support.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107497" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107497"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">3. Fit</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107356" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Running and lifting shoes must fit perfectly. A proper fit is critical for both comfort and performance. To discover the right fit, measure your feet and try on numerous sizes and styles.</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705413288466" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705413288466" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1705413288417" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1705413288417" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-l