ht: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107336" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107336"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">4. Durability</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107343" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107343" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Running and lifting shoes are subjected to a lot of wear and tear, so choosing shoes made of high-quality materials that can survive extensive use is critical.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107514" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673241107514"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">5. Brand Reputation</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107509" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107509" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Search for companies who have a solid reputation for providing high-quality running and lifting shoes. This might assist you avoid buying shoes that are poorly manufactured and do not give the required support and comfort.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677370402132" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1677370402132"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">6. Budget</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677370400206" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1677370400206" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Running and lifting shoes come at a variety of prices, so keep your budget in mind while selecting your shoes. Remember that investing in a high-quality pair of shoes can prevent damage and pain in the long run.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673326486980" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673326486980" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/a1446580-083c-4a00-95d9-9907fc229dd3/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/nike-metcon-lifting-shoes-review.jpg" alt="nike metcon lifting shoes review" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1024" height="683" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="nike metcon lifting shoes review" natural-width="1024" natural-height="683"></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1673241107335" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1673241107335" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107334" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107334"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107519" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107519"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Can You Use Running Shoes for Lifting?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107522" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107522"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Weightlifting can be done in running shoes, although they are not optimal. Running shoes are made for sports like running that require cushioning and shock absorption, whereas weightlifting shoes are made to provide a stable and supportive base for lifting large weights. Running shoes include cushioning that can absorb some of the power generated when lifting, potentially decreasing your ability to lift, as well as a heel-to-toe drop that can influence balance and stability. Although running shoes can be utilized momentarily, they are not recommended for long-term use if you wish to achieve your lifting goals.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107525" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107525"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Is There a Shoe That Is Good for Both Lifting and Cardio?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107524" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107524"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Sure, there are cross-training shoes that are suitable for both lifting and cardio exercises. These shoes are intended to give a balance of support, stability, and cushioning that will enhance both activities. These frequently have a flat sole and a wide base for stability while lifting, as well as adequate cushioning and flexibility for aerobic exercises. Cross-training shoes, on the other hand, may not provide the same level of support and features as dedicated lifting or running shoes. It's also critical to select a shoe that meets your unique demands and tastes, as well as your foot shape and size.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107520" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107520"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I Have Different Shoes for Lifting and Running?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673241107528" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673241107528"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="text-align: inherit !important;">Lifting and running shoes should be worn separately, since they are built with different features to facilitate the individual movements involved in each exercise. Running shoes are built for forward motion and have cushioning, flexibility, and breathability, but weightlifting shoes have a higher heel to help achieve a deeper squat posture and are meant to give a stable basis for lifting large weights. Lifting in running shoes can weaken stability and raise the chance of injury, whilst running in weightlifting shoes can be uncomfortable and affect running performance. Certain cross-training shoes, on the other hand, can give a decent balance of features for both activities. Finally, to enhance your performance and limit the chance of injury, buy s